The Nightmare Court would have taken over the whole swamp, if not for your actions. Safe travels, friend. 

—Laewyn

Salutations!

Tales of your exploits in Caledon Forest have spread far and wide, and one thing has become exceedingly clear: your determination and skill are unmatched. There's a whole world out there, waiting for someone like you.

Keep up the good work.

— Tyrian Explorers Society

Cotts wanted to send you this letter of thanks, but he was too sick to keep his paper clean. I don't know what you two are up to, but I can tell you that it's not working. The privateers are as rowdy as ever, and Penzan has been raving on and on about nonsense...as usual. 

—Sam Simmons, Crew Doctor, Penzan Privateers

I came up for air and noticed that the Corsair base is in disarray. Good job. I'd advise you not to linger, in case they catch onto what you've been doing over there.

—Agent Carter, Order of Whispers

Here's my obligatory letter of gratitude for your help, as protocol requires. Meaningless niceties aside, if you've taken any cursed treasure away from this site, it'll be on your head, not mine!

—Professor Michael Maciver, Durmand Priory
Hope You Didn't Take Any Treasure

Salutations,

Pardon the subject line, but I couldn't resist. I'm pleased to report that the drake situation is becoming somewhat managable. We're having fewer reports of drakes attacking travelers, which means I shouldn't have to sentence my Lionguard to certain doom on drake extermination detail. Surely we wouldn't have made such progress without you.

—Lionguard Tunnira

Sometimes you to need to invent your own scientific method. I call mine 'The Alchemical Method of Summoning Stones, by Inka.' It's a little wordy, but then, so am I."
—Scholar Inka"

The Durmand Priory has one of the necromancer's amulets and they've prepared a battery of tests to learn all they can about it. The tests will begin as soon as you join Yahala Scribepaw at the Priory's remote testing facility.

Rytlock and the orders of Tyria need more information about the necromancer Rissa's amulets. The Order of Whispers is standing by to steal the information they need from the Inquest, and Korukhan the Blacksmith is standing by for you to join their efforts.
